%h1 Sniphr

%p.big
  I'm up in your chromes, sniffin' yr snips!
  Sniphr is a Google Chrome extension that tracks the text you select as you browse the web.
  Each time you select a piece of text, Sniphr saves it. Think of it as a casual form of bookmarking.
  
%p.big
  = link_to("Step 1: Sign in with your Twitter account.", "/auth/twitter")

%p.big
  - if logged_in?
    = link_to("Step 2: Configure your domain whitelist.", settings_path) + " (optional)"
  - else
    Step 2: Configure a whitelist of sniph-able domains.

%p.big
  - if logged_in? && current_user.updated_at.present?
    = link_to("Step 3: Install the extension.", "https://chrome.google.com/extensions/detail/dgpgdcglcodcglcglbompkodmjnoobil")
  - else
    Step 3: Install the extension.
  

= sample_sniph_queries